1.title: Bigger, Better, Badder
1.plot: Jeff and Meg have big plans to grow Flat 12 Gallery. They hire a mechanic to help Eric, Jeff looks at more expensive cars - including a totally custom, 1962 Impala and they plan to attend a higher-end auction in Auburn, Indiana. Flat 12 is moving into riskier territory, but the rewards could be huge.

2.title: The Rarest Cars You'll Ever See
2.plot: Jeff and Meg take a trip to California to check out a pristine 1931 Chevrolet Victoria hot rod and find a bonus car to go along with it. Back in Lubbock, Eric and Luke slice and dice a six-wheeled monster military vehicle. And later, Jeff butts heads with Billy Hayes in a salesman showdown over a slick, black Ferrari Testarossa.

3.title: Three Great Cars - One Big Problem
3.plot: A search for a 1984 Mercedes reveals a collector with several classic cars, but none of them will start, which means Eric and Luke have to fix them before Meg finds out

4.title: This Screams Money!
4.plot: Jeff checks out a Cadillac DeVille on a tip from Tom; and pursues a Ferrari GTA that was owned by Shaquille O'Neal.

5.title: New Kids on the Auction Block
5.plot: The crew go to Indiana for one of the largest auctions of the year, but Jeff and Meg's enthusiasm is tempered by the unpredictability of the bidding.

6.title: Going... Going... Gone!
6.plot: The last day at the auction in Indiana is marred by a 1971 Jaguar that won't start.

7.title: Sales Contract Killers
7.plot: Jeff braces for a loss on a 1923 Buick; Eric and Luke work on a 1956 Bel Air. The teams works on Booking its biggest contract yet with Universal's Cabana bay beach Resort.

8.title: Jeff's Vice
8.plot: Jeff examines a Ferrari that allegedly vanished from the set of "Miami Vice." Also: Jeff tries to make a deal for a custom motorcycle.

9.title: Jeff Gets a Woodie
9.plot: A hotel with a 1960s theme hires Jeff and Meg to buy cars from that era, but Jeff's negotiations with a protégé for a 1957 "Woodie" wagon take a turn for the worse

10.title: Four in the Bag
10.plot: Four 1950s family cars are to be on display at a swanky resort in Florida, but Jeff is racing against the clock to make it happen.

11.title: Rejected!
11.plot: Jeff's deals fall through for a 1966 Jaguar Mark X and a 1970s Chevelle, but he can't dwell on his disappointment for too long because there's another auction on the horizon.

12.title: Going Flat Out
12.plot: Flat 12 pays for six slots at an auction in Missouri but they only have five cars, and two of them may not be ready.

13.title: No Bull Here!
13.plot: Jeff and Meg go to Florida to visit Rossion Automotive, a maker of high-performance sports cars that floats the idea of Flat 12 becoming a dealership. Meanwhile, Tom works out a deal that involves a 1955 Bel Air and a statue of a bull.

14.title: Little Red Corvette
14.plot: Jeff covets a 1969 Corvette that he envisions turning into a classic racer with fender flares from the seller. Later, a pair of iconic British convertibles catch Jeff's eye when he and Meg visit a huge car collection.

15.title: Go Big or Go Home
15.plot: Jeff pursues a Ferrari Mondial and a Camaro Z/28. Later, Jeff informs Meg he wants to stage an auto show and auction in Texas, but she balks at the price.

16.title: CARmageddon
16.plot: In the Season 3 finale, an event called Carmageddon in Lubbock, Texas, features a classic car show, an auto-cross race and an auction,

1.title: Flippin Ferraris
1.plot: Jeff and Perry pursue a 1981 Ferrari in Las Vegas in the premiere of the series about a pair of car aficionados who seek classic cars to flip. They also head to an auction to move inventory, including a motorcycle with ties to the "Terminator" movies.

2.title: Stacks of Cash and a Hidden Stash
2.plot: Jeff discovers priceless cars, including a 1969 Dickie Harrell Camaro 427, at a hidden compound in Midland Odessa, Texas. Also: Jeff and his father compete for a 1969 Chevy Camaro.

3.title: Fast and Furious Profits
3.plot: Jeff and Meg hope to score cars used in movies during a visit to Hollywood, but a tough negotiation with an old friend threatens their goal and the friendship itself. Later, Jeff competes against his father at an auction.

4.title: Lights, Cameras, Cars
4.plot: A major buyer puts in an order for American muscle cars; Jeff and Meg search for the 1940s-era automobiles that were seen in the movie "Gangster Squad"; an important purchase is damaged during transport.

5.title: Hot Rods and Hot Models
5.plot: Jeff, Meg and Perry travel to Las Vegas for an automotive trade show. Among their finds: a pristine 1965 Malibu; and two hot rods. They also take in a Long Beach swap meet, where Jeff becomes interested in a '71 Chevy "Frankentruck." Once they return to Lubbock, Meg arranges a pinup-girl photo shoot to market some of the cars. In other events, Jeff scrambles after his attempt to impress a European buyer backfires.

6.title: American Muscle Madness
6.plot: Jeff tours an airport hangar that's home to a 1965 Shelby Cobra, a WWII-era military jeep and a vintage jet fighter ejection seat; Jeff competes against his dad in an auction for a Boss Mustang.

7.title: Auction Fever
7.plot: The team prepares for a huge auction. Eric tricks out a 1931 hot rod while Meg and Jeff try to boost the value of a '53 Merc, but problems with both may cause the payday to be less than they hoped. A freak blizzard adds to their woes

8.title: California Dreamin'
8.plot: Jeff and Meg contemplate moving the shop to L.A. to take advantage of the bigger marketplace and, to that end, scout potential locations. Jeff also tries to make the trip pay for itself, but may lose big money instead.

1.title: A Tale of Two Chevys
1.plot: In the Season 2 premiere, Flat 12 Gallery prepares to open another location. In other events, Jeff sets out to transform a run-of-the-mill 1957 Chevrolet Bel Air so that it rivals his dad's beloved $100,000 Bel Air

2.title: Bayou Blitz
2.plot: The guys head to Louisiana, where a test drive ends in a fire; and they endure a boat ride in a thunderstorm. Among their finds: a 1978 Trans-Am and a pristine 1980 Kawasaki Z1 motorcycle.

3.title: Right Around the Corner
3.plot: Jeff and Matt check out an eclectic mix of old cars; and Jeff pulls a risky move with the seller in an attempt to secure a deal. In other events, Meg and Eric hone their selling chops at the shop; and Eric and Perry diagnose and fix a car with a leak.

4.title: Lights, Camera, Action, Cars!
4.plot: Jeff and Meg prepare for a visit from an auction representative by heading to California in search for unique cars. They meet with a yoga teacher who owns a British roadster; and check out a classic from a movie car warehouse

5.title: In Overdrive to Auction
5.plot: Jeff and the team prepare for an auction in New Orleans

6.title: Let the Good Times Roll
6.plot: At a New Orleans auction, a downpour threatens the team's freshly detailed cars.

7.title: More Power
7.plot: In Hollywood, Jeff checks out Tim Allen's private collection; and Jeff negotiates with colorful locals for an Italian super-car that's in bad shape.

8.title: Corvette Crazy
8.plot: Jeff buys an '82 Corvette, which his team prepares for auction; and butts heads with Meg over a low-mileage classic

9.title: The Ride of Frankenstein
9.plot: Jeff and Meg head to L.A., where Jeff haggles with an eccentric car builder who's offering a beefed-up Camaro and a BMW hot rod. He also tries to purchase a car used on "Mad Men."

10.title: Fast Deals, Furious Wheels
10.plot: Jeff hopes to buy a tribute Richard Petty race car from Roundman; and is surprised when a friend offers him a pristine Delorean.

11.title: Bucks Capacitor
11.plot: Jeff hopes to score some vehicles that appeared in the "Fast & Furious" movies; and meet with some shady men who are selling a dune buggy they claim was used in several films.

12.title: Texas Capital Gains
12.plot: Jeff chases leads in Austin, Texas, including a motorcycle and a highly collectible scooter from the 1940s. In other events, Jeff tries to sell a movie stunt car to a friend.

13.title: Camaro Cache
13.plot: Jeff contemplates buying a 1970 Camaro, but the deal hits a snag when the car won't start. However, Jeff then spots another Camaro on the property that he'd love to have, though the owner has no interest in selling it.

15.title: Put Your Money Where Your Mouth Is
15.plot: Roundman has a new Shelby GT500 that Jeff wants; and a family is interesting in buying Jeff's custom 1957 Chevy

16.title: Austin Auction Action
16.plot: The gang prepares several cars for auction, including a 1960 Bonneville, two Camaros, a Chevy C-10 and a Formula 400 with paint problems

imdb.plot outline: Jeff Allen and Perry Barndt are gamblers...their game, classic and exotic cars. They travel the country looking to buy and sell cars. Whether it's a rare Shelby Mustang or a one-of-a-kind Bugatti, the key is buy low and sell high, something that doesn't always happen. Selling cars is a dangerous business...but perhaps there's no greater danger than negotiating with your own dad. Tom Souter, Jeff's dad, runs his own classic car dealership right around the corner from Jeff's shop in Lubbock, Texas. They are not just regular trading partners; they are trading partners hell-bent on one-upmanship. Tom says doing a deal with his son is like being locked in a closet with a porcupine, "it's gonna hurt but you know it won't kill you."
